Growing up I flew from this airport for many bmx trips including my first trip as a pro rider. Back then I never would’ve thought that years later I’d be able to ride all the spots I saw as I walked through the terminal! Huge shoutout to @redbullusa & @jake_wooten for making the old MSY ( New Orleans ) airport into one of the most unique locations I’ve ever had the opportunity to ride my bike!

@grantcbmx isn’t afraid to film in the splash zone and @brocraiford is as dialed as it gets. Together they produced RETALIATE, one of three full parts Broc recently released. By now I’m sure you’ve seen all three and got them on repeat 🔥 Broc jumped in the @unclickedpodcast studio to watch and break down each part. @demarcuspaul is in the studio guest hosting along with @zachkrejmas who filmed INCINERATE. Now playing on ourbmx dot com and wherever you listen to podcasts. Shout out to @oskarblues for supporting the @unclickedpodcast #bmx #ourbmx #unclickedpodcast

Filmed by @brandongalosi 

Edited by @gumonthesidewalk 

My 4th part of the year is now featured in ALYK’s ‘25/8’ video. The crew specializes in having an eye for unique setups and paying close attention to the details beyond just getting the clip. The byproduct is a well thought out and cohesive viewing experience. It’s cool being featured in a video amongst some of the og’s! Special thanks to Robbie at @cultcrew , Galosi, and Damian for making this happen. I appreciate the opportunity to be included!

Had to be extra precise on this one! The ledge and brick area I was landing on were already slick from the light rain coming down. The wet leafs scattered around made it feel like I was landing on ice. I did end up loosing my footing on one of the attempts and ended up taking a dip in the near puddle. Thankfully walked away with the clip in the bag soon after the brief slip n slide! Haha 

📽️: @zachkrejmas

See ya 2023! Spent a good portion of this past year working on parts of myself I haven’t made a priority in a while! I wanted to ring in the new year being in the best shape I could possibly be, both physically and mentally! It’s been a humbling year to say the least but I want to give a very special thanks to all my friends and family for being there for me through one of the most challenging years I’ve had yet! Cheers to a new year feeling better than I ever have with some amazing people in my corner!
